        "question": "What drum kit did Nick Menza use on Countdown to Extinction?",
        "answer": "Nick Menza played a Tama Artstar II kit on Countdown to Extinction, recorded at Enterprise Studios in Burbank in 1992. The setup featured twin 22 by 16 inch bass drums, 10 and 12 inch rack toms, and 14 and 16 inch floor toms — a streamlined four-tom configuration compared to the five-tom sprawl he used on Rust in Peace. All shells were birch with die-cast hoops, giving the kit the attack and clarity needed to cut through the album's dense guitar arrangements while Max Norman's production delivered the bigger, more radio-ready drum sound the songs called for."
