        "question": "How commercially successful was Countdown to Extinction?",
        "answer": "Countdown to Extinction is the commercial high-water mark of Megadeth's career. It debuted at #2 on the Billboard 200 in July 1992, held back from the top spot only by Billy Ray Cyrus's \"Some Gave All,\" and has been certified 2x Platinum in the United States by the RIAA. The album spawned three career-defining singles — \"Symphony of Destruction,\" \"Sweating Bullets,\" and \"Foreclosure of a Dream\" — and earned a Grammy nomination for Best Metal Performance at the 1993 ceremony, where Nine Inch Nails ultimately won. It moved Megadeth from thrash-circuit headliner to arena act."
